Q-1
Stall Management
Write a program to create, update and delete stall details from database using ADO.NET.

[Note : Strictly adhere to the object oriented specifications given as a part of the problem statement.
Follow the naming conventions as mentioned. Create separate classes in separate files.]

Consider a class Stall with the following private attributes.
Data Type	Attributes
int	_id
string	_name
string	_category
string	_owner
The methods for getters, setters and constructors are given in the template code.
 
Consider a class StallBO and define the following method.
Method Name	Description
public bool InsertStall(Stall stall)	In this method, call the InsertStall() method in StallDAO and return the bool value indicating the status of insertion.
public bool UpdateStall(int stallId, string category)	In this method, call the UpdateStall() method in StallDAO and return bool value indicating the status of updation.
public bool DeleteStall(int stallId)	In this method, call the DeleteStall() method in StallDAO and return bool value indicating the status of deletion.
public void DisplayStalls()	In this method, call GetAllStall() method in StallDAO and display the stall details. If stall list is empty, display ‘No available stalls’

Consider a class StallDAO and define the following methods.
Method Name	Description
public bool InsertStall(Stall stall)	In this method, insert the stall object to stall table in database and return the insert status as boolean value.
public bool UpdateStall(int stallId, string category)	In this method, update category of a stall based on the stall id and return the update status as a boolean value.
public bool DeleteStall(int stallId)	In this method, delete the stall details from the stall table based on the stall id and return the delete status as a boolean value.
public List<Stall> GetAllStall()	In this method, get all the stall details from the stall table and convert it into list of stall objects. Return the list of stall objects.
 
Consider the class DBConnection and define the following method.
Method Name	Description
public static SqlConnection GetConnection()	This method is used to connect the Csharp application with mssql database.
Configure the database properties (fetch from mssql.xml) and return the connection object.
 
Consider the class Program. It includes the method Main.
In the Main method, read the stall details from the user. Display the menu and call the appropriate methods in StallBO to perform the requested operations.
Display “Inserted successfully” after every successful insertion of stall and same for update and delete.
Display ‘Invalid input’ if the updation and deletion of a stall is not successfull.
Display ‘Invalid input’ if the user selects invalid choice of menu.

The link to download the template code is given below
Code Template

To view the table data and the table structure, use script.sql given in the template code.
Table properties :
CREATE TABLE stall(
    id INT NOT NULL IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    category VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    owner VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

Use mssql.xml code to establish DB connection in C# application.
mssql.xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<mssql>
    <username>sa</username>
    <password>password</password>
    <host>localhost</host>
    <port>1433</port>
    <schema>StallManagement</schema>
</mssql>


Input and Output Format :
If the selected menu option is invalid then display “Invalid input”.
Display the stall details in insertion order.
Use the below format to display the stall details.
String.Format("{0,-5} {1,-15} {2,-15} {3}",  "Id", "Name", "Category", "Owner")
Refer sample input and output for formatting specifications.

[All text in bold corresponds to the input and the rest corresponds to output.]

