Q-2
Hall Management
Write a program to create, update and delete hall details from database using ADO.NET.

[Note : Strictly adhere to the object oriented specifications given as a part of the problem statement.
Follow the naming conventions as mentioned. Create separate classes in separate files.]

Consider the class Hall with the following private attributes.
Data type	Attributes
int	_id
string	_name
string	_mobileNumber
double	_costPerDay
string	_owner
The methods for getters, setters and constructors are given in the template code.

Consider the class HallBO and define the following methods
Method Name	Description
public bool InsertHall(Hall hall)	In this method, call the InsertHall() method in HallDAO and return the bool value indicating the status of insertion.
public bool UpdateHall(int hallId, double costPerDay)	In this method, call the UpdateHall() method in HallDAO and return bool value indicating the status of updation.
public bool DeleteHall(int hallId)	In this method, call the DeleteHall() method in HallDAO and return bool value indicating the status of deletion.
public void DisplayHalls()	In this method, call GetAllHall() method in HallDAO and display the hall details. If hall list is empty, display ‘No hall available’.

Consider the class HallDAO and define the following methods.
Method Name	Description
public bool InsertHall(Hall hall)	In this method, insert the hall object to hall table in database and return the insert status as bool value.
public bool UpdateHall(int hallId, double costPerDay)	In this method, update cost per day of a hall based on the hall id and return the update status as a bool value.
public bool DeleteHall(int hallId)	In this method, delete the hall details from the hall table based on the hall id and return the delete status as a boolean value.
public List<Hall> GetAllHall()	In this method, get all the hall details from the hall table and convert it into list of hall objects. Return the list of hall objects.
 
Consider the class DBConnection and define the following method.
Method Name	Description
public static SqlConnection GetConnection()	This method is used to connect the Csharp application with mssql database.
Configure the database properties (fetch from mssql.xml) and return the connection object.
 
Consider the class Program. It includes the method Main.
In the Main method, read the hall details from the user. Display the menu and call the appropriate methods in HallBO to perform the requested operations.
Display the message “Hall inserted successfully” after every successful insertion of hall and same for update and delete.
Display ‘Invalid hall id’ if the updation and deletion of a hall is not successfull.
Display ‘Invalid input’ if the user selects invalid choice of menu.

The link to download the template code is given below
Code Template

To view the table data and the table structure, use script.sql given in the template code.

Table properties :
CREATE TABLE hall(
    id INT NOT NULL IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    mobile_number VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    cost_per_day FLOAT NOT NULL,
    owner VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

Use mssql.xml code to establish DB connection.
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<mssql>
  <username>sa</username>
  <password>password</password>
  <host>localhost</host>
  <port>1433</port>
  <schema>HallManagement</schema>
</mssql>


Input and Output Format :
Display the hall details in insertion order.
Use the below format to display the hall details.
String.Format("{0,-5} {1,-20} {2,-15} {3,-10} {4}", "Id", "Name", "Mobile number", "Cost per day", "Owner")
Refer sample input and output for formatting specifications.

[All text in bold corresponds to the input and the rest corresponds to output.]

