Q-3-

Cake Shop
Write a program to create, update and delete cake details from database using ADO.NET.

[Note : Strictly adhere to the object oriented specifications given as a part of the problem statement.
Follow the naming conventions as mentioned. Create separate classes in separate files.]

Consider a class Cake with the following private attributes.
Data type	Attributes
int	_id
string	_name
string	_flavor
string	_weight
double	_price
The methods for getters, setters and constructors are given in the template code.

Consider a class CakeBO and define the following methods.
Method Name	Description
public bool InsertCake(Cake cake)	In this method, call the InsertCake() method in CakeDAO and return the bool value indicating the status of insertion.
public bool UpdateCake(int cakeId, double price)	In this method, call the UpdateCake() method in CakeDAO and return bool value indicating the status of updation.
public bool DeleteCake(int cakeId)	In this method, call the DeleteCake() method in CakeDAO and return bool value indicating the status of deletion.
public void DisplayCakes()	In this method, call GetAllCake() method in CakeDAO and display the cake details. If cake list is empty, display ‘No cake available’

Consider a class CakeDAO and define the following methods.
Method Name	Description
public bool InsertCake(Cake cake)	In this method, insert the cake object to cake table in database and return the insert status as boolean value.
public bool UpdateCake(int cakeId, double price)	In this method, update price of a cake based on the cake id and return the update status as a boolean value.
public bool DeleteCake(int cakeId)	In this method, delete the cake details from the cake table based on the cake id and return the delete status as a boolean value.
public List<Cake> GetAllCake()	In this method, get all the cake details from the cake table and convert it into list of cake objects. Return the list of cake objects.
 
Consider the class DBConnection and define the following method.
Method Name	Description
public static SqlConnection GetConnection()	This method is used to connect the Csharp application with mssql database.
Configure the database properties (fetch from mssql.xml) and return the connection object.
 
Consider the class Program. It includes the method Main.
In the Main method, read the cake details from the user. Display the menu and call the appropriate methods in CakeBO to perform the requested operations.
Display the message “Inserted successfully” after every successful insertion of cake details. Display the message for update and delete.
Display ‘Invalid cake id’ if the updation and deletion of a cake is not successfull.
Display ‘Invalid input’ if the user selects invalid choice of menu.

The link to download the template code is given below
Code Template

To view the table data and the table structure, use script.sql given in the template code.
Table properties :
create table cake(
    id int not null identity(1,1) primary key,
    name varchar(255) not null,
    flavor varchar(255) not null,
    weight varchar(255) not null,
    price float not null
);

Use mssql.xml code to establish DB connection in C# application.
mssql.xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<mssql>
    <username>sa</username>
    <password>password</password>
    <host>localhost</host>
    <port>1433</port>
    <schema>CakeManagement</schema>
</mssql>

Input and Output Format :
If the selected menu option is invalid then display “Invalid input”.
Display the cake details in insertion order.
Use the below format to display the cake details.
String.Format("{0,-5}{1,-15}{2,-15}{3,-10}{4}", "Id", "Name", "Flavor", "Weight", "Price")
Refer sample input and output for formatting specifications.

[All text in bold corresponds to the input and the rest corresponds to output.]

